<h1>@HI{{tte}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> <em>quote</em> <strong>@HI{{tte}}</strong>
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{tte}}</strong> is an informal version of the quotation marker @HI{{to}}.
When <strong>@HI{{tte}}</strong> is followed by @KJ{{say}}@HI{{u}},
then the meaning is "the person who is the topic says ...".
If there is no following verb then the meaning is ambiguous as the clause could mean "they say ...".
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KT{{je-nn}}ha@KJ{{jump}}ranai<strong>tte</strong>.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Jane said she wouldn't dance./They say Jane won't dance.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{me}}mo@KJ{{going}}kou<strong>tte</strong>@KJ{{think}}imashita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I wondered if I should go there too.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

